@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{org-ref-extras.el} extends @samp{org-ref}, the comprehensive citation and bibliography management package for Org mode. Rather than adding new commands, this package focuses exclusively on patching existing @samp{org-ref} functions to fix behaviors that interfere with a particular Bib@TeX{} formatting workflow.

The package uses @samp{el-patch} to make two targeted modifications:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Disable automatic filling after sorting.} The standard @code{org-ref-sort-bibtex-entry} command calls @code{bibtex-fill-entry} after sorting, which wraps long field values. This patch removes that call, preserving the original line structure of field values (@ref{Sorting without filling}).
@item
@strong{Remove redundant Year field from ISBN imports.} The @code{isbn-to-bibtex} command fetches Bib@TeX{} data from @samp{www.ebook.de}, which often includes both a @samp{date} and a @samp{Year} field. The patch strips the redundant @samp{Year} line before inserting the entry (@ref{ISBN import cleanup}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{org-ref} (including @samp{org-ref-isbn}) and @samp{el-patch}.

